  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "These were the ones that Margarita Higgins were looking for were not there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We found out they had been moved to Austria before we arrived and the-- Pastor Niemoller survived the war.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] I remember he-- in some of his remembrances, I've seen some of the writings, he said something about they persecuted the Jews and I said nothing; they persecuted the labor unions and I said nothing-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] --and then they came for me.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[LAUGHING] He made an observation something like that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he did speak out and that's the reason they came for him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But he survived and there apparently was no systematic execution of the-- of priests of various religions, although some were executed in the records for trying to lead a rebellion or speaking out, even when they're in prison camp.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Homosexuals were also discriminated against.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] --in our classification of prisoners, we did not try to identify those, if there were any, and I presume there were some.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I know they had a special marking.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Each prisoner was supposed to have a special marking on an emblem on his shoulder.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Jewish would have the star of David and the-- oh, various insignia were-- homosexuals had their own insignia.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But if there were any in Dachau, I never knew about it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And apparently, it was-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] --not an intensive drive, as near as I can gather-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] --because Ernst Rohm, who was the head of the Brown Shirts, the organization that put Hitler into power, was a homosexual.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Hitler had him killed, but not because he was homosexual, because he wanted him out of the way.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He considered Mr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Rohm too powerful.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
